('16b96c28-a49c-4588-9394-eb7ff3931ab2', 'post_essential_oil_14', 'en', 'Cajeput essential oil', '<p>Cajeput essential oil is actually a volatile oil obtained by distillation from the leaves of the myrtaceous trees Melaleuca leucadendron. The trees producing the oil are located throughout Maritime Southeast Asia and also over the hotter parts of the Australian continent. This particular oil is incredibly stinky, and it has the aroma of a combination of turpentine and camphor.</p>
